Date: Tue, 8 Apr 1997 19:17:38 +0100
From: Oz <Oz@upthorpe.demon.co.uk>
Subject: Re: PRO/AH> Salmonella infections - Australia (Victoria) (02)
In olden days when I was young hot weather tended to mean that food could
get quite hot if left out, even briefly. What it might do in a car beggars
belief. I do somewhat fear that forever blaming shops, manufacturing or
farms might be overlooking what happens to the food between shop and mouth.
We avoid blaming (or educating) the public at their peril.
I am also old enough to remember the removal of many (all?) preservatives
from foods due to health scares. At the time food technologists warned of
the danger of increased infections of food borne pathogens. Sometimes I
cannot help but believe they may have had a point.
--
O. Hotz de Baar
Farmer, Southern England, UK.
